however the director shall have experience in job placement, 21
school counseling, or primary and secondary education. 22
(C) Directors employed under division (B) of this section 23
shall do all of the following: 24
(1) Collaborate with OhioMeansJobs and other community 25
partners, as identified by the director, to identify available 26
jobs, apprenticeships, and internships in the community, and 27
engage students in career mentoring with community members; 28
(2) Determine the number of students that may participate 29
in the program at the district or school; 30
(3) Create an application and procedures to apply for the 31
program and, as a part of the application procedures, interview 32
students and administer an aptitude test, as selected by the 33
director, to assess their professional skills to determine a 34
student's eligibility and preparedness to participate in the 35
program; 36
(4) Offer dedicated and regular classroom instruction to 37
the maximum number of students possible in soft skills and 38
professional skills training, including problem-solving, time 39
management, creative and critical thinking, communication and 40
civility, and ethics. If a district or school currently offers 41
similar instruction the director shall collaborate with those 42
instructors, other appropriate school officials that have 43
commensurate experience, and professionals who support the 44
development of career and life pathways in the school. Students 45
may use instruction under division (B)(4) of this section to 46

